00:00:00.932 --> 00:00:02.791
- [Matt] GCN does science.

00:00:05.735 --> 00:00:07.336
- [Simon] #data.

00:00:07.787 --> 00:00:12.397
- A while ago, we tested the effects of a
bike weight on climbing speeds, but in a

00:00:12.397 --> 00:00:15.699
laboratory setting. And while this is
undeniably the most accurate way

00:00:15.699 --> 00:00:18.973
to test it, there's a big part of us
that still wants to see what the

00:00:18.973 --> 00:00:20.783
effect is out on the open road.

00:00:20.783 --> 00:00:23.769
- And what better place to do than here
on the Colle del Sestriere? The scene

00:00:23.769 --> 00:00:27.901
of many battles in the Tour de France
and the 2015 Giro d'Italia.

00:00:27.901 --> 00:00:31.522
- Yeah. So what we're going to do,
Matt and I are going to do two runs

00:00:31.522 --> 00:00:34.995
of this climb, each. Now, it's about eight
kilometers long, an average gradient

00:00:34.995 --> 00:00:39.882
of about 7%. I am going to use my Garmin
bike to power me to ride at consistent

00:00:39.882 --> 00:00:43.433
power both runs, and then I'm going to do
the second run with two kilograms

00:00:43.433 --> 00:00:47.280
of ballast added to my bike and then
we can compare the times directly.

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:50.893
- I'm going to do exactly the same but my
power meter is going to be in here,

00:00:50.893 --> 00:00:55.571
old school, all on feel because I think
that perception is still really valuable

00:00:55.571 --> 00:00:57.043
and very, very important.

00:00:57.043 --> 00:00:58.740
- Yeah, you calibrated this morning?

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:00.875
- It took me a bit of time
because obviously we're at altitude,

00:01:00.875 --> 00:01:02.994
but it's pretty much spot
on and I'm ready to go.

00:01:03.150 --> 00:01:04.233
- Let's do some pedaling.

00:01:04.462 --> 00:01:07.476
♪ [music] ♪

00:01:07.476 --> 00:01:12.376
- My bike weighs in at 6.920 kilograms
without weight, and then with a full water

00:01:12.376 --> 00:01:19.792
bottle, 7.595. Then finally, with ballast
added, it comes in at 9.505.

00:01:19.792 --> 00:01:23.967
So that's a differential of around two
kilograms taken into account the full

00:01:23.967 --> 00:01:30.614
water bottle on both runs. So round one,
the ballast bike, let's give it a nudge.

00:01:31.055 --> 00:01:34.068
♪ [music] ♪

00:01:47.226 --> 00:01:52.260
- Just trying to keep a nice rhythm, keep
my breathing controlled which is actually

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:57.850
harder than you think at altitude. But I
think I found a good level which I can

00:01:57.850 --> 00:02:02.633
sustain for the half an hour
effort, there abouts.

00:02:02.983 --> 00:02:06.019
♪ [music] ♪

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:11.219
- Okay then, first run, light bike.
Let's give it a go.

00:02:12.043 --> 00:02:15.113
♪ [music] ♪

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.442
For my support,
kind of feels like normal.

00:02:23.834 --> 00:02:26.862
♪ [music] ♪

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:36.846
Well, round one done.
That was pretty tough.

00:02:36.846 --> 00:02:38.380
