Sorry, I can't speak.

00:04:18.881 --> 00:04:19.730
- All right.

00:04:21.125 --> 00:04:24.410
Now the results are in,
but before we give you them,

00:04:24.410 --> 00:04:28.470
we must stress this is not a controlled
test. So this is purely for discussion

00:04:28.470 --> 00:04:31.690
only. We can't account for things
like wind or anything like that,

00:04:31.690 --> 00:04:36.040
but it is nevertheless very interesting.
On my bike, so I was riding to an average

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:41.770
power of 320 watts on both runs. I was 35
seconds slower with the heavier bike.

00:04:41.770 --> 00:04:45.180
So it doesn't actually sound like all that
much. It's only about 2% of my overall

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:47.450
time. But Matt on the other hand,
Matt was really interesting.

00:04:47.450 --> 00:04:52.120
- It was. Well, I went on the light bike.
I went one minute and three quarters

00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:56.253
quicker. Now that was for exactly the same
perceived effort so in relation to that,

00:04:56.253 --> 00:05:00.660
it was the pain in my legs and also
my breathing, and that remained the same

00:05:00.660 --> 00:05:04.050
for the whole of the each ride. And where
I noticed the difference was when the road

00:05:04.050 --> 00:05:08.590
pitched up above 7%, 8% gradient and the
bike felt far more responsive and I could

00:05:08.590 --> 00:05:11.560
use a bigger gear on the steeper parts.
I think that's where I made up the time.

00:05:11.560 --> 00:05:14.594
- Well, and even more interesting was that
it was your second run when you were

00:05:14.594 --> 00:05:17.144
on the lighter bike so one would have
thought that you had a bit of fatigue

00:05:17.144 --> 00:05:22.230
in your legs there. So, conclusions then.
Well, perhaps if we're after pure

00:05:22.230 --> 00:05:26.337
performance, clearly we can see that a
lighter bike is going to be faster on a

00:05:26.337 --> 00:05:30.370
climb but the difference isn't necessarily
as big as you'd think. But when it's

00:05:30.370 --> 00:05:34.100
out of pure enjoyment and perceived
effort, it made a huge difference.

00:05:34.100 --> 00:05:35.160
- It certainly did.

00:05:35.160 --> 00:05:39.960
- So, maybe there it is. A lighter bike
will make you go faster but it will feel

00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:43.550
even faster than that. So that's our
experience, but we'd be really interested

00:05:43.550 --> 00:05:46.324
